A.2 Proof of Theorem 5.3 (Discrete Noether)

Assume $G$ is a Lie group acting on $Q$ with infinitesimal generator $\xi_Q$. Invariance means $\mathcal{L}_\theta(g \cdot q, g \cdot q') = \mathcal{L}_\theta(q, q')$ for all $g \in G$. Differentiating at the identity:

